en_66310_0	An incident where two small children of the same family being killed after falling into a culvert at Egoda-hena-watta in Piliyandala in Kesbawa was reported yesterday.
en_66310_1	These two small children had fallen into a culvert that had been dug for constructing a culvert on the road newly constructed at Jaaliyagoda in Kesbawa.
en_66310_2	The two children had gone with their mother to  a tuition class and then  to a relative’s house.
en_66310_3	Reports say that subsequently the two children had played in the pit under construction for a culvert  using for their play a plantain tree trunk.
en_66310_4	The Piliyandala police said that the two children had fallen into the pit and been killed after getting stuck in the pit of mud.
en_66310_5	The two children thus killed were a 9-year old boy and a 7-year old girl who had been students of the Maakanda Sri Sudarshana School.
en_66310_6	Their bodies are now kept at the Piliyandala hospital mortuary.
